article.headline: Montana 68, Princeton 54
article.story:
MISSOULA (AP) -- Hollie Tyler scored a game-high 18 points to
lead Montana over a halftime disadvantage to beat Princeton 68-54
in Sunday's first round of the Lady Griz Holiday Classic.

Tyler also grabbed 10 rebounds for Montana along with Jody
McLeod. Julie Deming added 14 points and Crystal Baird had 10.

Montana (8-2) lost an early lead on a 3-pointer from the Tigers'
Casey Lockwood and ended the half trailing 28-26. Princeton (2-8)
had stretched that lead to five points when McLeod, Brooklynn
Lorenzen and Katie Edwards combined for a 9-0 run that put the
Grizzlies back in front.

The Tigers crept within 37-36 when Montana went on a 9-2 run and
Princeton never came close again.

Montana shot 36.1 percent from the field, compared to 39.2
percent for Princeton. The Tigers were outrebounded 50-38.

Rebecca Brown led Princeton with 16 points, while Lockwood added
11.
